    "updated_at": "2016-12-24T02:44:38Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Against my better judgement I went ahead and added support for Windows and Linux, hacky as they are.  On windows we obey the DPI slider in the system settings, and on linux players can run with e.g. `OPENRA_DISPLAY_SCALE=2 mono OpenRA.Game.exe`.\r\n\r\nCaveats:\r\n* I haven't been able to test switching between high/low DPI monitors on Windows or Linux.\r\n* Linux support is limited to windows-like scaling under X11, and won't work with the OSX-like scaling of Wayland."
  },
